TY  - JOUR
AU  - Fama, Eugene F
AU  - French, Kenneth R
T1  - The Value Premium
PY  - 2021
Y1  - 2021/03/01
DO  - 10.1093/rapstu/raaa021
JO  - The Review of Asset Pricing Studies
JA  - Rev Asset Pric Stud
VL  - 11
IS  - 1
SP  - 105
EP  - 121
SN  - 2045-9920
AB  - Value premiums, which we define as value portfolio returns in excess of market portfolio returns, are on average much lower in the second half of the July 1963–June 2019 period. But the high volatility of monthly premiums prevents us from rejecting the hypothesis that expected premiums are the same in both halves of the sample. Regressions that forecast value premiums with book-to-market ratios in excess of market (BM–BMM) produce more reliable evidence of second-half declines in expected value premiums, but only if we assume the regression coefficients are constant during the sample period.Received: January 21, 2020; editorial decision: July 21, 2020; Editor: Jeffrey Pontiff.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rapstu/raaa021
ER  - 



